# Pre-Edit Backup Policy (Always Apply)

Before editing any existing file, create a backup copy in the project root or a `backups/` folder.

## Backup Naming

- Use a deterministic timestamped name:
  - `zzz_<original_name>__pre_<YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS><ext>`
- Example:
  - `zzz_routing__pre_20260401_143022.py`

## Scope

- Applies to all manual code edits in this repository.
- If editing multiple files, create one backup per file before first edit.
- New files do not require a pre-edit backup.

## Session Tracking

- Keep a short list of touched files in session notes/output.
- At completion, report:
  - files backed up
  - files edited
  - any files intentionally skipped (with reason)

## Safety

- Never overwrite an existing backup file.
- If backup creation fails, stop and ask before proceeding.
